cerpt":"Razin Abi al-Nu\u2019man reported: Ali ibn Abi Talib, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhen you are asked about what you do not know, then flee.\u201d It was said, \u201cO leader of the faithful, how does one flee?\u201d Ali said, \u201cThat you say: Allah knows best.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Da\u0304rimi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32798,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/14\/prophet-teaches-ali-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":15477,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet teaches Ali what to say in distress","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 14, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali ibn Abi Talib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, taught me to say when I was afflicted with distress, \u201cThere is no God but Allah, the Forbearing, the Noble. Glory be to Allah, blessed is Allah the Lord of the Great Throne, and all\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34241,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/07\/06\/ali-do-not-rebuke\/","url_meta":{"origin":15477,"position":5},"title":"Ali on Blame: Do not excessively rebuke people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abi al-Sa\u2019ib reported: Ali ibn Abi Talib, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cDo not frequently scold others, for scolding leads to resentment and hatred and to